msgid "Priest description"
msgstr ""
"The priest is important for the group, but doesnâ€™t put himself in the way of\n"
"direct danger like the warrior. Instead, they perform vital tasks with their\n"
"hands at a safe distance. In the Raku world, priests submit bug tickets, write\n"
"tests and answer newbie questions on the #raku channel."

msgid "Mage"
msgstr ""

msgid "Mage description"
msgstr ""
"In the flurry of activity during a quest, the mages are the ones who wield\n"
"forceful spells in the form of new features in our implementations. The mages\n"
"know some pretty hefty incantations, but they speak in codes (like \"Haskell\",\n"
"\"Parrot\" or \"Lisp\") so that us mere non-initiates can only stand by in\n"
"admiration when they get going."

msgid "Healer"
msgstr ""

msgid "Healer description"
msgstr ""
"Some people are in the group to make sure the group is doing well, and that\n"
"no-one is critically low on hit-points. Discussions can sometimes get heated\n"
"or sharp, by which point we're very glad to have the people around who are\n"
"specially trained to see beyond the ego and help us focus on the important\n"
"parts of the picture. We simply need to be reminded at times, that we're\n"
"(as S01 expresses it) \"a bunch of ants all cooperating (sort of) to haul food\n"
"toward the nest (on average)\". We don't need to agree always on everything,\n"
"but keeping the group coherent is important, and healers do their magic in\n"
"the background to help us with that."

